dcterms:description: The PHYDYAS prototype filter is used in the context of FBMC-based massive MIMO systems to transmit QAM symbols, providing a high bandwidth efficiency and resilience to synchronization errors.
dcterms:title: PHYDYAS prototype filter

dcterms:description: The Tap delay line-C (TDL-C) from the 5G channel model is utilized to generate channels for simulating the performance of FBMC-based massive MIMO systems, providing a PDP based on a normalized RMS delay spread.
dcterms:title: Tap delay line-C (TDL-C) from 5G channel model

dcterms:description: This dataset involves channel reciprocity modeling and performance evaluation, which is critical for understanding the effects of imperfect channel reciprocity in massive MIMO systems.
dcterms:title: Channel reciprocity modeling and performance evaluation
